["Adolescent Mental Health", "Browse our site in Jordan and Syria now.", "23 October 2019", "Key facts", "One in six people is between 10 and 19 years old.", "Mental health conditions account for 16% of the global burden of disease and injury among people aged 10 to 19 years.", "Half of mental health conditions begin at age 14, but most of these cases are undetected and untreated.", "(1)", "Globally, depression is one of the leading causes of illness and disability among adolescents.", "Suicide is the third cause of death for people between the ages of 15 and 19.", "The consequences of not taking care of adolescents' mental health ailments extend into adulthood, causing both physical and mental health impairment and limiting the chances of a satisfactory life in adulthood.", "an introduction", "Adolescence (10-19 years) is a unique and formative stage.", "Multiple physical, emotional and social changes, including exposure to poverty, abuse or violence, can make adolescents vulnerable to mental health problems.", "Promoting adolescents' psychological well-being and protecting them from harmful experiences and risk factors that may affect their potential for development are not only essential to their safety during adolescence, but also to their physical and psychological health in adulthood.", "Determinants of mental health", "Adolescence is a critical period for developing and maintaining social and emotional habits important for mental well-being.", "This includes following healthy sleep patterns, getting regular exercise, developing coping skills, problem-solving and interpersonal skills, and learning to manage emotions.", "Supportive environments within the family, school, and broader community are also important.", "It is estimated that 10-20% of adolescents worldwide suffer from mental health conditions, but the level of diagnosis and treatment of these disorders is still low (1).", "There are several factors that determine mental health outcomes.", "The more risk factors adolescents are exposed to, the greater the potential impact on their mental health.", "Among the factors that can contribute to stress during adolescence are the desire for greater independence, pressure to conform with peers, exploration of gender identity, and increased access to and use of technology.", "Media influence and gender norms can increase the discrepancy between an adolescent\u2019s lived reality and their perceptions or future aspirations.", "Other important determinants of adolescent mental health are the quality of his family life and his relationships with his peers.", "Moreover, violence (including cruel father and mother treatment and harassment) and socio-economic problems are recognized mental health risks.", "Children and adolescents are particularly vulnerable to sexual violence, which is clearly linked to harmful consequences for mental health.", "Some adolescents are considered at greater risk of mental health conditions due to their living conditions, stigmatization, discrimination or exclusion, or lack of access to quality support and services.", "This includes adolescents in human and vulnerable situations, adolescents with chronic disease, autism spectrum disorder, intellectual disability or other neurological disorders, pregnant teens, teenage parents / teenage mothers, or adolescents who are early and / or forcibly married, and orphans. And adolescents belonging to ethnic or national minorities or other groups that suffer from discrimination.", "Adolescents with mental health conditions are also particularly vulnerable to social exclusion, discrimination and stigmatization (which affect willingness to seek help), education-related difficulties, risk-taking behaviors, physical ill-health and human rights violations.", "Emotional disturbances", "Emotional disturbances usually appear during adolescence.", "In addition to depression or anxiety, teens with emotional distress may also feel irritable, frustrated or angry.", "Symptoms can overlap between several forms of emotional distress, and are interspersed with rapid and unexpected changes in mood and emotional outbursts.", "Younger adolescents may also develop symptoms of a physical nature due to psychological causes such as stomach pain, headache or nausea.", "Globally, depression is the fourth leading cause of illness and disability among adolescents between the ages of 15 and 19, and the fifteenth leading cause for adolescents between the ages of 10 and 14 years.", "Anxiety is the ninth leading cause of illness and disability among adolescents between the ages of 15 and 19 years, and the sixth leading cause for adolescents between the ages of 10 and 14 years.", "Affective disorders may significantly affect a teen\u2019s performance in specific areas, such as work and school attendance.", "Distancing from society may exacerbate isolation and loneliness.", "Depression at its worst can lead to suicide.", "Behavioral disorders in children", "Childhood behavioral disorders are the second leading cause of disease burden among young adolescents between the ages of 10 and 14 years, and the eleventh leading cause among older adolescents between the ages of 15 and 19.", "Adolescence may be the stage where rules and boundaries are tested.", "Childhood behavioral disorders include ADHD (characterized by difficulty paying attention, hyperactivity, and acting without regard for the consequences, which are behaviors inappropriate for a person's age) and conduct disorder (involving symptoms of destructive or difficult behaviors).", "Childhood behavioral disorders can affect adolescents' education, and may lead to criminal behavior.", "Eating disorders", "Eating disorders usually appear during adolescence and adulthood, and affect females more than males.", "Eating disorders such as anorexia nervosa, bulimia nervosa and binge eating disorder are characterized by harmful eating behaviors such as caloric restriction or binge eating.", "Eating disorders are harmful to health and often coexist with depression, anxiety, and / or substance abuse.", "Psychosis", "Disorders that present with symptoms of psychosis usually appear in late adolescence or early adulthood.", "Symptoms of psychosis can include hallucinations or delusions.", "Experiences of psychosis can impair an adolescent's ability to participate in daily life and education, and often cause stigma or human rights violations.", "Suicide and self-harm", "It is estimated that 62,000 adolescents died in 2016 as a result of self-harm.", "Suicide is the third leading cause of death among older adolescents (ages 15-19).", "About 90% of the world's adolescents live in low or middle income countries, but more than 90% of suicides among adolescents relate to adolescents living in these countries in particular.", "The risk factors for suicide are multifaceted, and range from harmful use of alcohol, exposure to childhood abuse, stigma that prevents people from seeking help, and obstacles to obtaining the care and means they need.", "Communication about suicidal behavior via digital media is a recent concern for this age group.", "Risk Behaviors", "Many risk-taking behaviors that pose a health risk, such as drug use or risky sexual behaviors, begin during adolescence.", "Risk-taking behaviors can constitute an unhelpful strategy for dealing with poor mental health, and they may have a dire impact on the psychological and physical well-being of an adolescent.", "Globally, the prevalence of bouts of binge drinking among adolescents between the ages of 15 and 19 was 13.6% in 2016, bearing in mind that males are more vulnerable to this than others.", "Tobacco and cannabis use is an additional concern.", "In 2016, estimates based on available data from 130 countries indicated that 5.6% of adolescents between the ages of 15 and 16 had used cannabis at least once in the previous year [2], while many adult smokers smoked their cigarettes. The first is before they reach the age of 18 years.", "The commission of violence is a risky behavior and can increase the likelihood of decreased academic achievement, injury, involvement in crime, or death.", "Interpersonal violence was the second leading cause of death in older teens in 2016.", "Health promotion and prevention", "Interventions aimed at promoting mental health and preventing its disorders aim to enhance the individual's ability to control their emotions, improve alternatives to risk-taking behaviors, gain flexibility in dealing with difficult situations and adversities, and strengthen supportive social environments and social networks.", "These programs require a multi-tiered approach that involves diverse platforms, such as digital media, health or social care institutions, schools, or the community, and various strategies to reach adolescents, especially adolescents who are most at risk.", "Early detection and treatment", "It is extremely important to meet the needs of adolescents with specific mental health disorders.", "Avoiding institutionalization and excessive medical interventions, prioritizing non-pharmacological approaches, and respecting children's rights in line with the United Nations Convention on the Rights of the Child and other human rights instruments are essential factors for adolescents.", "The WHO Mental Health Gap Action Program (mhGAP) provides a set of evidence-based guidance for non-specialists to enable them to identify priority mental health conditions in under-resourced countries and support better treatment.", "Organization response", "The organization works to develop strategies, programs and tools to help governments respond to adolescent health needs.", "Here are the most relevant resources:", "Global Acceleration of Action for Adolescent Health: Guidance to Support Country Implementation", "Global Strategy on Women's, Children's and Adolescent Health 2016-2030", "Mental Health Action Plan 2013-2020", "Mental Health Gap Action Program (mhGAP)", "In the